001package org.biopax.validator;
002
003import java.util.*;
004
005import org.biopax.paxtools.controller.SimpleEditorMap;
006import org.biopax.paxtools.model.BioPAXLevel;
007import org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Level3Element;
008import org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.ControlledVocabulary;
009import org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.UnificationXref;
010import org.biopax.paxtools.normalizer.Normalizer;
011import org.biopax.paxtools.util.ClassFilterSet;
012import org.biopax.psidev.ontology_manager.*;
013import org.biopax.validator.api.CvRestriction;
014import org.biopax.validator.api.beans.Validation;
015
016import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;
017
018
019/**
020 * A BioPAX L3 controlled vocabulary context-aware term validation rule.
021 *
022 * @author rodch
023 */
024public abstract class CvTermsRule<T extends Level3Element> extends AbstractCvRule<T>
025{
026
027  /**
028   * Constructor.
029   *
030   * TODO: (a feature) to allow using a path in 'property' parameter (e.g., "modificationFeature/modificationType")
031   *
032   * @param domain biopax property domain (object)
033   * @param property biopax property name
034   * @param restrictions restrictions on the controlled vocabulary (ontology) terms, given biopax property context
035   */
036  public CvTermsRule(Class<T> domain, String property, CvRestriction... restrictions)
037  {
038    super(domain, property, restrictions);
039  }
040
041  @PostConstruct
042  @Override
043  public void init() {
044    super.init();
045    this.editor = (property != null && !ControlledVocabulary.class.isAssignableFrom(domain))
046      ? SimpleEditorMap.L3.getEditorForProperty(property, this.domain)
047      : null;
048  };
049
050
051  public void check(Validation validation, T thing) {
052    // a set of CVs for this rule to validate
053    Collection<ControlledVocabulary> vocabularies = new HashSet<>();
054
055    // if the editor is null, we expect a ControlledVocabulary object!
056    if(editor == null) {
057      vocabularies.add((ControlledVocabulary)thing);
058    } else {
059      vocabularies.addAll((Collection<ControlledVocabulary>) editor.getValueFromBean(thing));
060    }
061
062    // shortcut
063    if(vocabularies.isEmpty()) return;
064
065    // text to report in any CV error case
066    String cvRuleInfo = ((editor != null) ? " property: "
067      + property : "") + " " + restrictions.toString();
068
069    // check each CV terms against the restrictions
070    for (ControlledVocabulary cv : vocabularies)
071    {
072      if (cv == null) {
073        logger.warn(thing
074          + " referes to 'null' controlled vocabulary (bug!): "
075          + ", domain: " + domain + ", property: " + property);
076      } else if(cv.getTerm().isEmpty()) {
077        /* won't report/fix what other rules (e.g., 'controlledVocabularyTermCRRule') or Normalizer do */
078      }
079      else {
080        //TODO: check if multiple terms are synonyms (equivalent)
081
082        final Set<String> badTerms = new HashSet<>(); // initially - none
083        final Map<String, Set<OntologyTermI>> noXrefTerms = new HashMap<>();
084        //original terms set to iterate over (to avoid concurrent modification exceptions - other rules can modify the set simultaneously)
085        final Set<String> terms = Collections.unmodifiableSet(new HashSet<>(cv.getTerm()));
086
087        // first, check terms (names) are valid
088        for(String name : terms)
089        {
090          if(!getValidTerms().contains(name.toLowerCase())) {
091            // save to report/delete/replace the invalid term later
092            badTerms.add(name);
093          }
094        }
095        // report but keep original perhaps illegal terms
096        if (!badTerms.isEmpty()) {
097          String badTermInfo = badTerms.toString();
098          error(validation, thing, "illegal.cv.term", false, badTermInfo, cvRuleInfo);
099        }
100
101        /* check if unif. xref.id points to invalid term,
102         * and, if so, report 'illegal.cv.xref' error
103         */
104        final Set<UnificationXref> badXrefs = new HashSet<>();
105        for (UnificationXref x : new ClassFilterSet<>(
106          cv.getXref(), UnificationXref.class))
107        {
108          OntologyTermI ot = ontologyUtils.getOntologyManager().findTermByAccession(x.getId());
109          if(ot == null || !getValidTerms().contains(ot.getPreferredName().toLowerCase())) {
110            badXrefs.add(x);
111          }
112        }
113        // report wrong uni.xrefs
114        if(!badXrefs.isEmpty()) {
115          String bads = badXrefs.toString();
116          // report as not fixed error case (won't fix/remove such xrefs, keep original)
117          error(validation, thing, "illegal.cv.xref", false, bads, cvRuleInfo);
118        }
119
120        // check valid terms have a uni.xref
121        for(String name : terms)
122        {
123          // only for valid terms
124          if(getValidTerms().contains(name.toLowerCase())) {
125            // check if there is the corresponding unification xref
126            Set<OntologyTermI> ots = ontologyUtils
127              .getOntologyManager().searchTermByName(name.toLowerCase(), getOntologyIDs());
128            assert(!ots.isEmpty()); // shouldn't be, because the above getValidTerms() contains the name
129            boolean noXrefsForTermNameFound = true; // next, - prove otherwise is the case
130            terms: for(OntologyTermI term : ots) {
131              String id = term.getTermAccession();
132              // search for the xref with the same xref.id
133              for (UnificationXref x : new ClassFilterSet<>(
134                cv.getXref(), UnificationXref.class)) {
135                if(id.equalsIgnoreCase(x.getId()))  {
136                  noXrefsForTermNameFound = false;
137                  break terms; // exit this and outer loops!
138                }
139              }
140            }
141
142            if(noXrefsForTermNameFound)
143              noXrefTerms.put(name, ots); //store terms to fix later (to generate xrefs)
144          }
145        }
146
147        // note: at this point, 'noXrefTerms' (valid terms only) map is defined...
148        if (!noXrefTerms.isEmpty()) {
149          String noXrefTermsInfo = noXrefTerms.toString();
150          boolean fixed = false;
151
152          if(validation.isFix()) {
153            /*
154             * However, it's not so trivial to fix by adding the xrefs, because:
155             * 1) no reference to the parent Model here available
156             *    (thus the validator must detect and add new objects automatically! [done!])
157             * 2) having the chance of creating several xrefs with the same RDFId requires
158             *    a special care or follow-up merging, as simply adding them to a model will
159             *    throw the "already have this element" exception!); and other rules
160             *    can also generate duplicates...
161             * 3) risk that a rule generating/adding a new element may cause
162             *    other rules to interfere via AOP and prevent changes in quite
163             *    unpredictable manner (...bites its own tail)
164             * 4) multiple terms (accession numbers) can result from searching by (synonym) name
165             *
166             *    Well, let's try to fix, anyway (and modifying ValidatorImpl as well)!
167             *    That's awesome!
168             */
169            Set<OntologyTermI> validTermIs = ontologyUtils.getValidTerms(this);
170            for (String name : noXrefTerms.keySet()) {
171              //get previously saved valid ontology term beans by name
172              Set<OntologyTermI> ots = noXrefTerms.get(name);
173              //get only top (parent) valid terms
174              Set<OntologyTermI> topvalids = new HashSet<>();
175              for (OntologyTermI term : ots) {
176                // skip terms that are not applicable although having the same synonym name
177                if(validTermIs.contains(term)) {
178                  OntologyAccess ont = ontologyUtils.getOntologyManager().getOntology(term.getOntologyId());
179                  //if term's parents does not contain any of these terms
180                  if(Collections.disjoint(ots, ont.getAllParents(term))) {
181                    topvalids.add(term);
182                  }
183                }
184              }
185              Set<String> added = new HashSet<>();
186              for (OntologyTermI term : topvalids) {
187                String ontId = term.getOntologyId();
188                String db = ontologyUtils.getOntologyManager().getOntology(ontId).getName();
189                String id = term.getTermAccession();
190                // auto-create and add the xref to the cv;
191                // generate an URI in the same namespace
192                String uri = Normalizer.uri(cv.getUri() + "_", db, id, UnificationXref.class);
193                if(!added.contains(uri)) {
194                  added.add(uri);
195                  UnificationXref ux = BioPAXLevel.L3.getDefaultFactory()
196                    .create(UnificationXref.class, uri);
197                  ux.setDb(db);
198                  ux.setId(id);
199                  cv.addXref(ux);
200                  fixed = true; // 99% true ;-)
201                  noXrefTermsInfo += "; " + id + " added!";
202                }
203              }
204            }
205          }
206
207          // report
208          error(validation, thing, "no.xref.cv.terms",
209            fixed, noXrefTermsInfo, cvRuleInfo);
210        }
211
212        //if in the fixing mode,
213        if (validation != null && validation.isFix()
214          //and there were some errors found,
215          && !(badTerms.isEmpty() && noXrefTerms.isEmpty()))
216        {
217          //then add/infer the valid preferred term from the unification xrefs -
218          Set<String> addTerms = createTermsFromUnificationXrefs(cv);
219          if (!addTerms.isEmpty()) {
220            cv.getTerm().addAll(addTerms);
221          }
222        }
223
224      }
225    }
226  }
227
228  //discover valid terms by unification xrefs (invalid xrefs won't get you anything)
229  private Set<String> createTermsFromUnificationXrefs(
230    ControlledVocabulary cv)
231  {
232    Set<String> inferred = new HashSet<>();
233    for (UnificationXref x : new ClassFilterSet<>(
234      cv.getXref(), UnificationXref.class))
235    {
236      OntologyTermI ot = ontologyUtils.getOntologyManager().findTermByAccession(x.getId());
237      //if found and valid
238      if (ot != null && getValidTerms().contains(ot.getPreferredName().toLowerCase())) {
239        inferred.add(ot.getPreferredName());
240      }
241      else if(ot == null)
242        logger.warn("No term found by the xref.id: " + x.getId());
243      else
244        logger.debug("Invalid (for this CV context) term: " + x.getId());
245    }
246
247    return inferred;
248  }
249
250}
